gy%2Farticleshow%2F103840618.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China's%20promotion%20of%20the%2019th%20Asian%20Games%20as%20the%20'Smart'%20Games%20is%20a%20common%20first%20impression%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20AI%20headquarters%20in%20Hangzhou%2C%20where%20the%20term%20'Smart'%20is%20widely%20used%20to%20describe%20the%20event.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22JASPREET%20SAHNI%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20'Jaane%20Jaan'%2C%20Director%20Sujoy%20Ghosh%20Tries%20Too%20Hard%20to%20Impress%20His%20Audience%20But%20Fails%20to%20Engage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21175930%2Fimage-1331.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDirector%20Sujoy%20Ghosh%20has%20always%20been%20a%20curious%20case%20for%20Hindi%20cinema.%20Gloriously%20nutty%20to%20be%20dismissed%20%5Beven%20in%20misfires%20like%20his%20recent%20%3Cem%3ELust%20Stories%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20segment%5D%2C%20and%20yet%20undercooked%20during%20several%20key%20moments.%20A%20great%20grip%20over%20the%20air%20he%20creates%20in%20scenes%2C%20but%20also%20an%20imitative%20quality%20that%20seems%20to%20have%20set%20in%20since%20his%20first%20%E2%80%98blockbuster%E2%80%99%20in%20%3Cem%3EKahaani%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2012).%20Since%20Vidya%20Balan%20pulled%20the%20rug%20from%20under%20all%20of%20us%2C%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Ghosh%20has%20made%20one%20sequel%2C%20remade%20a%20Spanish%20thriller%2C%20and%20now%20followed%20it%20up%20with%20another%20adaptation%20of%20a%20popular%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EDevotion%20of%20Suspect%20X%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Keigo%20Higashino%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20also%20the%20inspiration%20behind%20Vasan%20Bala%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMonica!%20O%20My%20Darling%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJaane%20Jaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20borrowing%20its%20name%20from%20the%20haunting%20Laxmikant-Pyarelal%20number%2C%20sung%20by%20Lata%20Mangeshkar%20and%20filmed%20on%20Helen%20in%20%3Cem%3EInteqam%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1969)%20%E2%80%93%20ends%20up%20more%20of%20as%20an%20acting%20showcase%20%5Bfor%20at%20least%20two%20of%20its%20three%20leads%5D%20rather%20than%20the%20detective%20piece%20it%20is%20meant%20to%20be.%20The%20premise%20of%20Higashino%E2%80%99s%20novel%20also%20served%20as%20source%20material%20for%20the%20wildly%20successful%20%3Cem%3EDrishyam%3C%2Fem%3E%20franchise.%20One%20wonders%20if%20Ghosh%20is%20going%20to%20mine%20the%20same%20source%20material%20and%20if%20so%2C%20what%20else%20will%20he%20bring%20to%20it.%20A%20fresh%20point-of-view%3F%20Some%20smart%20choices%20that%20subvert%20the%20audience%E2%80%99s%20expectations%20in%20important%20scenes%3F%20Unfortunately%2C%20very%20little%20in%20%3Cem%3EJaane%20Jaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20feels%20born%20out%20of%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESujoy%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20fingerprints%20are%20all%20over%20this%20adaptation%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20is%20visible%20in%20some%20very%20deliberate%20choices.%20Like%20the%20way%20he%20weaponises%20his%20protagonist%E2%80%99s%20femininity.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20recurring%20theme%20since%20the%20first%20%3Cem%3EKahaani%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20in%20%3Cem%3EBadla%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20where%20he%20recast%20the%20male%20protagonist%20with%20Taapsee%20Pannu.%20It%20makes%20the%20divorced%20single%20mother%20of%20Maya%20D%E2%80%99Souza%20(Kareena%20Kapoor%20Khan)%20almost%20tailor-made%20for%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20oeuvre.%20The%20film%20is%20set%20in%20misty%20Kalimpong%20%E2%80%93%20where%20everything%20appears%20hazier%20than%20usual%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20another%20one%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20favourites.%20%3Cem%3EKahaani%202%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2016)%20was%20partly%20shot%20here%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FGHX6yT9Lxfo%3Fsi%3DQmGtpfgKakgjLFKe%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EMaya%20and%20her%20daughter%2C%20Tara%2C%20are%20neighbours%20to%20Naren%20(a%20scene-stealing%20Jaideep%20Ahlawat)%20%E2%80%93%20a%20gifted-but-depressed%20Math%20teacher%20at%20a%20local%20high%20school.%20Maya%20runs%20a%20cafe%2C%20Naren%20goes%20there%20every%20morning%20to%20collect%20his%20egg%20fried%20rice%20to%20carry%20as%20his%20lunch.%20Maya%E2%80%99s%20colleague%20at%20the%20cafe%20%E2%80%93%20a%20wasted%20Lin%20Laishram%20%E2%80%93%20is%20relegated%20to%20giggling%20like%20a%20teenager%20each%20time%20Naren%20enters%20the%20cafe.%20They%20know%20Naren%20likes%20Maya%2C%20they%20tell%20her.%20She%20dismisses%20them%2C%20even%20though%20she%20sees%20his%20blushing%20pockmarked%20face%20everyday.%20%E2%80%9CLike%20the%20sun%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20character%20says%20at%20one%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20when%20Maya%2C%20Tara%20and%20Naren%E2%80%99s%20world%20seems%20almost%20too%20blissful%2C%20a%20shadow%20lurks.%20Maya%E2%80%99s%20ex-husband%20(Saurabh%20Sachdeva)%20returns%20and%20you%20can%20immediately%20see%20the%20trauma%20he%20has%20inflicted%2C%20with%20a%20single%20expression%20on%20Maya%E2%80%99s%20face.%20A%20crime%20is%20committed%2C%20a%20body%20needs%20to%20be%20disposed%20of.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20interestingly%20staged%20scene%20of%20crime%2C%20one%20that%20isn%E2%80%99t%20clinically%20premeditated%2C%20but%20one%20that%E2%80%99s%20slowly%20built%20towards%2C%20concluding%20with%20a%20few%20seconds%20of%20anguish%20and%20desperation.%20Kapoor-Khan%20is%20excellent%20in%20the%20scene%20%E2%80%93%20conveying%20the%20feeling%20of%20being%20violated%20by%20a%20man%E2%80%99s%20mere%20presence%2C%20and%20remaining%20tactful%2C%20as%20her%20observant%20neighbour%20comes%20to%20check%20up%20on%20her%20as%20a%20corpse%20lies%20in%20her%20living%20room.%3Cins%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20superb%20mix%20of%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20Kapoor-Khan%20known%20for%20her%20starry%20charisma%20is%20supposed%20to%20take%20on%20the%20more%20studied%20styles%20of%20Vijay%20Varma%20and%20Ahlawat.%20On%20paper%2C%20it%20is%20a%20combination%20made%20in%20heaven.%20However%2C%20it%20rarely%20lives%20up%20to%20its%20potential.%20An%20awkwardness%20remains%20between%20the%20three%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20the%20performances%20never%20blending%20in%20together%2C%20instead%20remaining%20as%20three%20distinct%20elements%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20scene.%20Naren%E2%80%99s%20mathematical%20analogies%20feel%20forced%20and%20amateurish%20in%20some%20scenes.%20Most%20of%20these%20scenes%20feel%20tentative%20%E2%80%93%20uncertain%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ehow%20much%20math%20is%20too%20much%20math%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20blockbuster%20audience.%20Vijay%20Varma%20%E2%80%93%20rarely%20trusted%20with%20such%20%E2%80%98positive%E2%80%99%20characters%20%E2%80%93%20smartly%20employs%20his%20charming%2C%20rom-com%20lead%20persona%20as%20a%20front%20to%20uncover%20the%20rot%20beneath%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20major%20problem%20with%20Sujoy%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EJaane%20Jaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20even%20while%20perfectly%20%E2%80%98consumable%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98engaging%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20moment%20with%20good%20moodiness%20and%20lovely%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20never%20becomes%20particularly%20memorable.%20A%20%E2%80%98reveal%E2%80%99%2C%20two-thirds%20into%20the%20film%2C%20about%20why%20Naren%20has%20been%20helping%20Maya%20and%20Tara%20%E2%80%93%20never%20really%20hits%20you%20with%20a%20wallop%20of%20unexpected%20warmth%20in%20a%20cold%20film%20like%20this.%20It%20is%20apparent%20from%20the%20first%20scene%20itself.%20The%20inter-cutting%20of%20an%20interrogation%20with%20a%20martial%20arts%20duel%20feels%20like%20the%20film%20is%20trying%20too%20hard%20to%20draw%20attention%20to%20its%20craft.%20The%20visual%20language%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20severe%20Japanese%20manga%20hangover%2C%20Avik%20Mukhopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20frames%20trying%20hard%20to%20mimic%20those%20panels.%20It%20feels%20vacuously%20stylish%20in%20more%20than%20one%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENot%20every%20detective%20drama%20needs%20to%20reinvent%20the%20wheel%20like%20Park%20Chan-wook%20did%20in%20%3Cem%3EDecision%20To%20Leave%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022).%20It%20is%20possible%20to%20remain%20faithful%20to%20the%20tropes%20and%20still%20end%20up%20with%20a%20respectable%20and%20compelling%20film.%20%3Cem%3EJaane%20Jaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20seems%20obsessed%20with%20delivering%20catharsis%20to%20its%20audience%2C%20without%20caring%20about%20how%20it%20gets%20there.%20A%20detective%20story%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20care%20about%20the%20little%20details%2C%20is%20arguably%20one%20of%20the%20most%20agonising%20viewing%20experiences.%20Sujoy%20Ghosh%20is%20still%20in%20nowhereland.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695299479000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21175930%2Fimage-1331.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fin-jaane-jaan-director-sujoy-ghosh-tries-too-hard-to-impress-his-audience-but-fails-to-engage%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inspired%20by%20a%20Japanese%20detective%20novel%2C%20the%20film%20fails%20to%20work%20on%20the%20little%20details%20and%20concentrates%20too%20much%20on%20style.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fin-jaane-jaan-director-sujoy-ghosh-tries-too-hard-to-impress-his-audience-but-fails-to-engage%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rwandan%20serial%20killer%20who%20hid%20bodies%20in%20kitchen%20pleads%20guilty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695299193000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F9C4F%2Fproduction%2F_131151004_rwandaserialkiller.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-