2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-659441%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar.%20Photo%3A%20Screengrab%20via%20YouTube%2FNews9%20Live%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20web%20portal%20titled%20its%20programme%20%E2%80%98Our%20Men%20In%20Shadows%20Rock%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20interviewed%20a%20retired%20senior%20Army%20officer%20who%20said%20the%20killings%20showed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20dawn%20of%20a%20new%20India%E2%80%9D%20had%20come.%20Another%20online%20portal%20declared%3A%20%E2%80%9CParamjit%20Singh%20Panjwar%20shot%20dead%3A%20Keep%20Calm%20and%20Trust%20the%20Armed%20Forces%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20also%20floated%20the%20theory%20that%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20ISI%20could%20have%20carried%20out%20the%20hits%2C%20as%20these%20men%2C%20purported%20%E2%80%9CPakistan%20ISI%20agents%E2%80%9D%2C%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20Indian%20security%20agencies%20by%20Amritpal%20Singh%2C%20whose%20Khalistani-style%20movement%20in%20Punjab%20ended%20with%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Famritpal-surrenders-himself-to-punjab-police-to-be-shifted-to-assam-soon%5C%22%3Earrest%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.%20All%20such%20posts%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwhoever%20it%20was%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20had%20scored%20big%20from%20the%20killings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20a%20mainstream%20Indian%20weekly%20trod%20similar%20ground.%20It%20blamed%20inter-gang%20warfare%20for%20the%20killing%2C%20but%20could%20not%20contain%20itself%20from%20projecting%20this%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cswift%20counter-terrorist%20operation%20by%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%9D%20that%20had%20inflicted%20a%20setback%20to%20an%20alleged%20Pakistan%20plan%20for%20a%20new%20Khalistan%20project%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CNijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%20proves%20that%20UK%2C%20Canada%2C%20Pakistan%20no%20longer%20safe%20havens%20for%20pro-Khalistani%20fugitives%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20publication%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theweek.in%2Fnews%2Fworld%2F2023%2F06%2F19%2Fkhalistan-tiger-force-chief-hardeep-singh-nijjar-shot-dead-in-canada.html%5C%22%3Eheadlined%20the%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20allegation%2C%20many%20pointed%20to%20Western%20double%20standards%20%E2%80%93%20they%20cause%20death%20and%20destruction%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20Iraq%2C%20and%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20take%20out%20our%20terrorists%20without%20being%20scolded%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFive%20Eyes%20vs%20%3Cem%3Eteesri%20aankh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Delhi%2C%20which%20wants%20to%20be%20seen%20rubbing%20shoulders%20at%20the%20high%20table%20with%20the%20G7%20even%20as%20it%20claims%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20south%E2%80%9D%2C%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20has%20created%20a%20dissonance%20in%20the%20post-G20%20narratives%20about%20India%2C%20its%20influence%20and%20clout%2C%20its%20convening%20power%2C%20and%20its%20bridging%20capabilities.%20All%20this%20because%20India%20has%20worked%20hard%20to%20project%20itself%20as%20a%20land%20of%201.5%20billion%20people%20that%20is%20not%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20thinks%20of%20itself%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Western%20security%2Fintelligence%20alliance%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20talk%20that%20it%20should%20be%20inducted%20into%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20partnership%20between%20Australia%2C%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20Canada%20and%20New%20Zealand.%20But%20some%20of%20these%20security%20agencies%20have%20been%20wary%20for%20a%20while%20of%20their%20Indian%20counterparts%20even%20if%20the%20political%20leadership%20has%20gone%20all%20out%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20Modi%20government.%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20accusation%20is%20unlikely%20to%20increase%20confidence%20levels.%20For%20reasons%20not%20clear%2C%20the%20R%26amp%3BAW%20station%20chief%E2%80%99s%20post%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%20which%20fell%20vacant%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20filled%20as%20the%20host%20government%20is%20yet%20to%20agree%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20this%20columnist%20pointed%20out%20earlier%2C%20greater%20influence%20brings%20a%20higher%20bar%20and%20more%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadas-allegations-will-bring-unwanted-attention-on-indian-immigrants-abroad%5C%22%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20Allegations%20Will%20Bring%20Unwanted%20Attention%20on%20Indian%20Immigrants%20Abroad%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENot%20the%20first%20accusation%20of%20%E2%80%9Cinterference%E2%80%9D%20by%20Canada%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20own%20problems%20with%20R%26amp%3BAW%20go%20back%20decades.%20But%20as%20recently%20as%202018%2C%20in%20a%20federal%20court%20in%20Canada%2C%20India%20was%20accused%20of%20%E2%80%9Cinterference%E2%80%9D%20in%20that%20country%E2%80%99s%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20recently%20as%202018%2C%20Canadian%20media%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalnews.ca%2Fnews%2F6823170%2Fcanadian-politicians-targeted-indian-intelligence%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20(IB)%20had%20attempted%20to%20use%20money%20and%20disinformation%20through%20an%20Indian%20citizen%3Cb%3E%20%3C%2Fb%3Eto%20%E2%80%9Ccovertly%20influence%E2%80%9D%20Canadian%20politicians%20to%20support%20Indian%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20came%20to%20light%20when%20the%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20a%20journalist%2C%20identified%20only%20as%20AB%20and%20%E2%80%9Ceditor-in-chief%E2%80%9D%20in%20court%20documents%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20acting%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20two%20Indian%20intelligence%20agencies.%20He%20had%20applied%20to%20emigrate%20to%20Canada%20%E2%80%93%20his%20wife%20and%20daughter%20were%20already%20Canadian%20citizens%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20role%20as%20a%20paid%20influencer%20of%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20the%20IB%20came%20up%20during%20checks%20on%20his%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20application%20was%20turned%20down%2C%20but%20a%20Canadian%20federal%20court%20later%20overturned%20the%20charge%20and%20allowed%20him%20to%20stay.%20He%20was%20questioned%20threadbare%20in%20court%20about%20his%20involvement%20with%20Indian%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20would%20eventually%20allow%20him%20to%20stay%20in%20Canada%2C%20but%20this%20was%20perhaps%20the%20first%20%E2%80%9Cpublicly%E2%80%9D%20alleged%20instance%20of%20clandestine%20foreign%20influence%20targeting%20Canadian%20politicians.%20Delhi%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20the%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHistory%20of%20bad%20blood%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20Royal%20Canadian%20Mounted%20Police%2C%20a%20law-enforcing%20agency%2C%20also%20performed%20the%20main%20intelligence%20role.%20As%20allegations%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20mounted%20against%20what%20was%20principally%20a%20police%20organisation%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20to%20set%20up%20the%20Canadian%20Security%20Intelligence%20Service%20(CSIS).%20The%20CSIS%20came%20into%20existence%20in%201984%2C%20just%20a%20year%20before%20the%20Kanishka%20bombing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20circumstances%20in%20which%20it%20was%20created%20and%20the%20botched%20investigation%20into%20the%20Kanishka%20bombing%2C%20CSIS%20and%20R%26amp%3BAW%20fell%20out%20quickly.%20The%20presence%20of%20a%20large%20Sikh%20diaspora%20in%20Canada%2C%20and%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rights-based%20approach%20to%20the%20Khalistani%20activists%20among%20them%2C%20has%20been%20a%20major%20irritant%20in%20ties%2C%20surfacing%20every%20now%20and%20then%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221201%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM.png%201201w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM-300x114.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM-1024x391.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-532477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ER%26amp%3BAW%E2%80%99s%20logo.%20Illustration%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECSIS%20redlines%2C%20R%26amp%3BAW%20withdraws%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20too%20well%20known%20that%20at%20the%20time%2C%20the%20CSIS%20wanted%20R%26amp%3BAW%20to%20sign%20off%20on%20a%20MoU%20listing%20do%E2%80%99s%20and%20don%E2%80%99ts%20for%20foreign%20intelligence%20operatives%2C%20which%20the%20Indian%20agency%20refused%20to%20do.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20IB%20did%20not%20post%20anyone%20in%20Canada.%20A%20semblance%20of%20Indian%20intelligence%20presence%20in%20Canada%20was%20maintained%20through%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Security%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%2