on%20cuts%20by%20Russia%20and%20autumn%20refinery%20maintenance.%20The%2018.73%20million%20tonnes%20of%20imports%20in%20August%20is%204%25%20lower%20than%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20imports%20in%20August%20were%20the%20lowest%20since%20November%202022.%20However%2C%20imports%20last%20month%20were%20higher%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%20by%206%25%20in%20comparison%20to%20August%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fcompanies%2Findias-crude-oil-imports-slip-to-10-month-low-in-august-2023%2Farticle67327160.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Line%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Petroleum%20Planning%20and%20Analysis%20Cell%20(PPAC)%20said%20the%20imports%20fell%20for%20the%20third%20consecutive%20month%20in%20August%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cvoluntary%20production%20cuts%20by%20Russia%E2%80%9D%2C%20also%20impacting%20its%20most%20sought-after%20medium%20sour%20grade%20Ural.%20Ural%20imports%20from%20Russia%20to%20India%20in%20August%20slipped%20to%20their%20lowest%20levels%20since%20January%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20reduction%20in%20imports%2C%20traders%20in%20India%20say%2C%20is%20due%20to%20smaller%20discounts%20on%20the%20Urals%20grade%20and%20the%20decreased%20appetite%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Indian%20refiners%20owing%20to%20planned%20autumn%20maintenance%20at%20some%20refineries.%20It%20is%20also%20due%20to%20reduced%20domestic%20demand%20in%20the%20country%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20rainy%20season%20until%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20dip%20in%20imports%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20monthly%20bill%20on%20crude%20oil%20rose%2C%20from%20%2410.3%20billion%20in%20July%20to%20%2410.9%20billion%20in%20August%20given%20that%20production%20cuts%20by%20Russia%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20hiked%20global%20crude%20prices.%20However%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20import%20bill%20in%20August%20was%20lower%20on%20an%20annual%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%20this%20year%2C%20Brent%20Crude%20was%20sold%20at%20an%20average%20of%20%2486.22%20per%20barrel%20in%20the%20global%20market%20compared%20to%20%2480.05%20in%20July%202023%20and%20%2499.99%20per%20barrel%20in%20August%202022.%20As%20for%20India%2C%20the%20basket%20crude%20price%20was%20averaged%20at%20%2486.43%20per%20barrel%20in%20August%202023%20against%20%2480.37%20during%20July%202023%20and%20%2497.40%20in%20August%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20(IEA)%20noted%20that%20the%20shipments%20to%20China%20and%20India%20dipped%20to%203.9%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20in%20August%202023%20from%204.7%20mb%2Fd%20in%20April%20and%20May%202023%20but%20accounted%20for%20more%20than%20half%20the%20total%20volumes.%20It%20also%20observed%20that%C2%A0the%20top%20two%20crude%20oil%20consumers%20globally%20accounted%20for%2080%25%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20total%20exports%20during%20May-July%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20senior%20oil%20marketing%20executive%2C%20quoted%20by%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Line%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20oil%20in%20the%20upcoming%20festive%20season%2C%20October-December%2C%20would%20spike%20owing%20to%20increased%20industrial%2C%20mining%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20farm%20activity.%20The%20official%20also%20said%20preparations%20for%20the%20festival%20season%20by%20firms%20in%20the%20fast-moving%20consumer%20goods%20(FMCG)%20and%20fast-moving%20consumer%20durables%20(FMCD)%20industry%20could%20also%20increase%20the%20demand%20for%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695283223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F04193929%2Fimage-966.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Findias-crude-oil-imports-fall-to-10-month-low-in-august-due-to-production-cuts-by-russia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20imports%20in%20August%20were%20the%20lowest%20since%20November%202022%20due%20to%20autumn%20refinery%20maintenance%20by%20Russia.%20India's%20monthly%20bill%20on%20crude%20oil%2C%20however%2C%20rose%20from%20%2410.3%20billion%20in%20July%20to%20%2410.9%20billion%20in%20August.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Findias-crude-oil-imports-fall-to-10-month-low-in-august-due-to-production-cuts-by-russia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hunger%20%E2%80%98Shocking%20Stain%20on%20Humanity%2C%20Epic%20Human%20Rights%20Violation%E2%80%99%3A%20UN's%20Guterres%20at%20SDG%20Summit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21131157%2FGuterres.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EUnited%20Nations%C2%A0Secretary-General%20Antonio%20Guterres%20on%20Monday%20told%20those%20present%20in%20New%20York%20for%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fun-sustainable-development-goals-losing-the-race%2Fa-66879154%5C%22%3ESustainable%20Development%20Goals%C2%A0summit%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20that%20the%20world%20needs%20a%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20rescue%20plan.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20text%20of%20commitment%20to%20the%2017%C2%A0Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20relate%20to%20almost%20all%20aspects%20of%20politics%20and%20livelihood%20and%20are%20primarily%20aimed%20at%20ending%20extreme%20poverty%20and%20hunger%20%E2%80%93%20was%20passed%20unanimously%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUN%20member%20states%20adopted%20the%20SDGs%20in%202015%2C%20committing%20at%20the%20time%20to%20achieving%20them%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%202023%20summit%2C%20a%20group%20of%20nations%20led%20by%20Russia%20had%20vowed%20to%20block%20passages%20but%20ultimately%20dropped%20the%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fantonio-guterres%2Ft-41524150%5C%22%3ESecretary-general%20Guterres%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20only%20about%2015%25%20of%20the%20goals%20%E2%80%93%20from%20eliminating%20extreme%20poverty%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20improving%20education%20and%20health%20provision%2C%20providing%20clean%20water%20and%20sanitation%20to%20all%2C%20and%20ensuring%20access%20to%20decent%20work%20and%20economic%20growth%20%E2%80%93%20are%20on%20track%20and%20warned%20that%20in%20some%20cases%20there%20had%20even%20been%20backsliding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20chief%C2%A0said%3A%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20SDGs%20aren%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20list%20of%20goals.%20They%20carry%20the%20hopes%2C%20dreams%2C%20rights%20and%20expectations%20of%20people%20everywhere.%20In%20our%20world%20of%20plenty%2C%20hunger%20is%20a%20shocking%20stain%20on%20humanity%C2%A0and%20an%20epic%20human%20rights%20violation.%20It%20is%20an%20indictment%20of%20every%20one%20of%20us%20that%20millions%20of%20people%20are%20starving%20in%20this%20day%20and%20age.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGerman%20Chancellor%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Folaf-scholz%2Ft-57304267%5C%22%3EOlaf%20Scholz%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0bemoaned%20the%C2%A0lack%20of%20progress%20and%20told%20those%20gathered%20Monday%C2%A0that%20developing%20countries%20expected%20support%20from%20wealthier%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProgress%20on%20many%20SDGs%20%E2%80%98stagnant%20or%20rolling%20backwards%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20difficulty%20of%20meeting%20such%20lofty%20goals%2C%20Laurel%20Patterson%2C%20spokesperson%C2%A0for%C2%A0the%20United%20Nations%20Development%20Programme%2C%20echoed%20Guterres%E2%80%99%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CProgress%2C%20as%20you%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20across%20the%20board%2C%20is%20certainly%20not%20where%20we%20expected%20it%20to%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20Patterson%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20cases%20%5Bit%20is%5D%20stagnant%20and%20rolling%20backwards.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20she%20claimed%20the%20SDGs%20remained%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20best%20opportunity%20for%20us%20as%20a%20global%20community%20to%20move%20forward.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPatterson%20pointed%20to%20poor%20nations%20spending%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20much%20of%20their%20budgets%20on%20servicing%20debt%20than%20on%20social%20welfare%20as%20an%20argument%20for%20debt%20cancellation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20that%20when%20%E2%80%9Cfiscal%20space%20is%20incredibly%20constrained%E2%80%9D%2C%20issues%20like%20climate%20change%20get%20pitted%20against%20poverty%20relief%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20she%20struck%20a%20strong%20note%20of%20caution%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20what%20development%20looks%20like%20and%20how%20progress%20is%20measured.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20electrification%20spreads%2C%20she%20said%2C%20so%20does%20energy%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20what%20comes%20across%20all%20of%20our%20reports%20%E2%80%93%2072%20out%20of%20the%2095%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20is%20that%20carbon%20emissions%20are%20moving%20in%20the%20wrong%20direction.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20actually%20increased%20since%202019%20and%20these%20are%20indeed%20troubling%20patterns.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20numbers%20and%20current%20trajectories%2C%20Patterson%20remains%20optimistic%20about%20the%20prospects%20of%20progress%20in%20New%20York%2C%20saying%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20combination%20of%20choices%2C%20leadership%2C%20political%20will%20and%20investment%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20within%20our%20hands.%20Those%20are%20choices%20that%20are%20possible%20for%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAddressing%20representatives%20from%20many%20of%20the%20193%20countries%20in%20New%20York%20to%20attend%20the%20General%20Assembly%20%E2%80%93%20which%20formally%20begins%20Tuesday%20and%20lasts%20one%20week%20%E2%80%93%20South%20African%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20an%20indictment%20of%20every%20one%20of%20us%20that%20millions%20of%20people%20are%20starving%20in%20this%20day%20and%20age.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20achievement%20of%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20depends%20on%20the%20fundamental%20reform%20of%20global%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20political%20relations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funs-guterres-hunger-is-an-epic-human-rights-violation%2Fa-66849579%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdw.com%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695282614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21131157%2FGuterres.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhunger-shocking-stain-on-humanity-says-antonio-guterres-at-sdg-summit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22United%20Nations%20secretary-general%20Antonio%20Guterres%20has%20called%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bglobal%20rescue%20plan%26quot%3B%20as%20precious%20few%20of%20the%20world's%2017%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDG)%20are%20making%20progress.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhunger-shocking-stain-on-humanity-says-antonio-guterres-at-sdg-summit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Obstinacy%20of%20Caste%20Followed%20Sikh%20Immigrants%20to%20Britain%20Too%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20142924%2FIMG_4546.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%20Ujjal%20Dosanjh%E2%80%99s%20new%20novel%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Past%20Is%20Never%20Dead%3Cem%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Speaking%20Tree%20Books.%20The%20book%20explores%20the%20impact%20of%20casteism%20on%20family%20life%20within%20the%20Sikh%20community%20in%20mid-20th%20century%20England.%20Even%20as%20it%20exposes%20the%20obstinacy%20of%20caste%2C%20the%20novel%20pays%20tribute%20to%20the%20courage%20and%20tenacity%20of%20the%20human%20spirit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Our%20ancestors%20would%20slaughter%20you%20people%20at%20the%20altar%E2%80%A6%20Our%20orders%20were%20to%20kill%20you%E2%80%A6remember%20that%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20the%20voice%2C%20as%20if%20they%E2%80%99d%20done%20him%20a%20favour%20by%20letting%20him%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20voice%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20voice%20that%20had%20spoken%20to%2C%20or%20rather%20at%2C%20him%20%E2%80%93%20had%20constantly%20hurled%20obscenities%20for%20what%20seemed%20like%20two%20days%20now.%20The%20vehicle%20in%20which%20they%20travelled%20sounded%20and%20felt%20like%20a%20small%20delivery%20van.%20It%20eventually%20dumped%20him%20on%20a%20gravel%20road%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20voice%20had%20instructed%20its%20companions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20489px)%2085vw%2C%20489px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21112356%2FThe-Past-is-Never-Dead_Revised_15March.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22489%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21112356%2FThe-Past-is-Never-Dead_Revised_15March.jpg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21112356%2FThe-Past-is-Never-Dead_Revised_15March-196x300.jpg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21112356%2FThe-Past-is-Never-Dead_Revised_15March-667x1024.jpg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674060%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Past%20is%20Never%20Dead.%20Ujjal%20Dosanjh%2C%20Speaking%20Tiger%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20minutes%20of%20lying%20inert%2C%20counting%20to%20two%20hundred%20and%20not%20to%20a%20thousand%20as%20he%20had%20been%20told%2C%20he%20removed%20his%20blindfold%20and%20opened%20his%20eyes%20and%20realized%20he%20was%20several%20miles%20away%20from%20home.%20In%20the%20dark%20and%20cold%20winter%20night%20he%20walked%20through%20the%20fields%2C%20bushes%20and%20across%20short-cuts.%20His%20limbs%20were%20near%20frozen.%20He%20found%20the%20pay%20phone%20he%20had%20remembered%20seeing%20earlier%20once%20by%20the%20road%20he%20was%20on%20now%20and%20called%20a%20taxi%20which%20took%20him%20home%20to%202%20St%20Leonard%E2%80%99s%20Ave%2C%20Bedford.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20his%20room%2C%20he%20wrapped%20himself%20in%20blankets%2C%20sat%20on%20his%20bed%20and%20looked%20out.%20Across%20the%20street%2C%20beyond%20the%20four-foot-tall%20brick%20wall%2C%20stood%20the%20deserted%20St%20John%E2%80%99s%20Railway%20Station%20and%20a%20red%20telephone%20booth%20near%20its%20entrance.%20He%20had%20used%20the%20telephone%20there%20scores%20of%20times.%20His%20ears%20remembered%20the%20clanking%20of%20the%20coins%20falling%20through%20the%20slot.%20The%20steadily%20falling%20snow%20appeared%20less%20than%20white%2C%3Cbr%3E%20discoloured.%20The%20station%20lampposts%20shone%20dim%2C%20much%20dimmer%20than%20usual.%20He%20prayed%20for%20a%20storm%E2%80%94a%20rainstorm%2C%20typhoon%2C%20earthquake%2C%20snowstorm%2C%20any%20storm.%20Anything!%20Something%20to%20wash%20everything%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20mysterious%20disappearance%20of%20over%20twenty-four%20hours%2C%20he%20had%20just%20returned%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Everything%20all%20right%2C%20son%3F%20Can%20I%20come%20in%3F%E2%80%99%20said%20Udho%20after%20knocking%20on%20his%20bedroom%20door%2C%20his%20voice%20muffled.%20Kalu%20heard%20the%20lump%20in%20Udho%E2%80%99s%20throat.%20He%20jumped%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20locked%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98No%2C%20Bhapa.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20see%20you%20in%20the%20morning.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20already%20told%20you%2C%20everything%E2%80%99s%20all%20right%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said%2C%20clutching%20the%20doorknob%20tightly%20in%20his%20right%20hand.%20His%20head%20touched%20one%20of%20his%20turbans%20hanging%20by%20the%20hook%20on%20the%20door.%20His%20body%20trembled%20as%20he%20turned%20to%20look%20at%20the%20mirror%20on%20the%20dresser.%20He%20thrust%20his%20clenched%20fist%20into%20it.%20The%20mirror%20cracked%2C%20but%20no%20shards%20fell%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Son%2C%20what%20was%20that%20noise%3F%20Everything%20all%20right%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKalu%20put%20his%20hands%20on%20his%20heart%2C%20afraid%20his%20father%20would%20hear%20its%20agitated%20pounding.%20He%20knew%20his%20father%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20believed%20a%20word%20he%20had%20said.%20The%20countless%20fragments%20of%20the%20fractured%20mirror%20reflected%20his%20naked%20body%2C%20dissected%20by%20the%20cracks.%20His%20hands%20moved%20from%20his%20heart%20to%20his%20head.%20The%20touch%20felt%20odd%20to%20his%20hands.%20He%20looked%20into%20the%20mirror%20again.%20It%20showed%20no%20hair%20on%20the%20face%2C%20the%20head%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20body%2C%20except%20at%20the%20crotch%20and%20some%20by%20the%20armpits.%20His%20legs%20wobbled%20under%20him.%20His%20hands%20moved%20to%20feel%20his%20neck%20and%20its%20hairless%20small.%20He%20noticed%20the%20marks%20of%20the%20turban%20on%20his%20forehead.%20His%20facial%20skin%20that%20normally%20hid%20under%20his%20turban%20was%20lighter%20compared%20to%20the%20darker%20brown%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20face.%20The%20black%20birth%20mark%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20his%20forehead%20stared%20at%20him%3B%20without%20the%20Sikh%20turban%2C%20the%20hair%20on%20his%20head%20and%20beard%2C%20the%20birth%20mark%20was%20visible%2C%20and%20his%20Chamarhood%20felt%20exposed.%20In%20the%20corner%20of%20his%20eye%2C%20he%20could%20see%20the%20solitary%20bulb%20hanging%20from%20the%20wire%20on%20the%20ceiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20thrust%20his%20fists%20into%20his%20eyes%20and%20turned%20away%20from%20the%20mirror.%20When%20he%20dropped%20his%20fists%2C%20his%20eyes%20opened%20to%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20wall%20above%20the%20headboard.%20Framed%20portraits%20of%20Ravidas%20and%20Ambedkar%2C%20deemed%20deities%20for%20the%20untouchables%2C%20looked%20down%20at%20him.%20In%20the%20dim%20light%20of%20the%20ceiling%20bulb%2C%20they%20looked%20anything%20but%20godlike.%20The%20garlands%20around%20their%20necks%20reeked%20of%20mortality%3B%20like%20nooses%2C%20they%20screamed%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKalu%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20turned%20to%20the%20small%20framed%20black-and-white%20photo%20of%20Udho%20on%20the%20bedside%20table.%20He%20seemed%20to%20jump%20out%20of%20the%20frame%2C%20dressed%20as%20Kalu%20remembered%20him%20in%201942.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUjjal%20Dosanjh%20was%20born%20in%20the%20Jalandhar%20district%20of%20Punjab%20in%201946.%20He%20emigrated%20to%20the%20UK%20in%201964%20and%20from%20there%20to%20Canada%20in%201968.%20He%20was%20Premier%20of%20British%20Columbia%20from%202000%20to%202001%20and%20a%20Liberal%20Party%20of%20Canada%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20from%202004%20to%202011%2C%20including%20a%20period%20as%20Minister%20of%20Health%20and%20Minister%20Responsible%20for%20Multiculturalism%2C%20Human%20Rights%20and%20Immigration.%20In%202003%20he%20was%20awarded%20the%20Pravasi%20Bharatiya%20Samman%2C%20the%20highest%20honour%20conferred%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20on%20overseas%20Indians.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695281434000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20142924%2FIMG_4546.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-obstinacy-of-caste-followed-sikh-immigrants-to-britain-too%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'He%20looked%20into%20the%20mirror%20again.%20It%20showed%20no%20hair%20on%20the%20face%2C%20the%20head%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20body...'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-obstin